        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mt-3 text-[15px]" style="max-width:70ch;">Decades of <a href="https://alexfoundation.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-clay font-medium underline decoration-clay/30 hover:decoration-clay">documented cognition research</a> made the Congo African Grey the bird people picture when they hear "the smartest parrot in the world." At C.A.Gs in Midland, TX, every <a href="/congo-african-grey-for-sale/" class="text-clay font-medium underline decoration-clay/30 hover:decoration-clay">Congo African Grey we place</a> is hand-fed from the nest box, DNA-sexed, and CITES Appendix I documented — the proof behind the reputation.</p>
