        <h5 class="font-sora font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide text-green mt-6 mb-1.5">What Is the Congo's Scientific Name — Psittacus erithacus?</h5>
        <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed text-[15px]" style="max-width:70ch;"><em>Psittacus erithacus</em> is the formal binomial for the Congo African Grey, native to the rainforests of West and Central Africa and listed on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grey_parrot" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-clay font-medium underline decoration-clay/30 hover:decoration-clay">CITES Appendix I as a protected species</a>. Every Congo we place is U.S. captive-bred and never wild-caught.</p>
